Feature: REST API Endpoints

  Scenario: POST /api/register creates user with required fields
    Given API endpoint POST /api/register exists
    When Request body contains name and email
    Then Response status code is 200

  Scenario: POST /api/register fails with missing name
    Given API endpoint POST /api/register exists
    When Request body omits name field
    Then Response status code is 400

  Scenario: POST /api/register fails with missing email
    Given API endpoint POST /api/register exists
    When Request body omits email field
    Then Response status code is 400

  Scenario: GET /api/users retrieves all users
    Given Users are registered in the system
    When GET request is made to /api/users
    Then Response status code is 200

  Scenario: PUT /api/users/:id updates user
    Given User with ID exists
    When PUT request is made with valid data
    Then Response status code is 200

  Scenario: DELETE /api/users/:id removes user
    Given User with ID exists
    When DELETE request is made to /api/users/{id}
    Then Response status code is 200